WEBVTT

1
00:01:38.598 --> 00:01:39.891
Oh.

2
00:01:43.562 --> 00:01:45.814
Oh, my gosh.

3
00:04:36.860 --> 00:04:37.986
What's going on?

4
00:04:38.069 --> 00:04:40.363
No time to explain. Run away.

5
00:04:45.410 --> 00:04:46.995
Oh, hey, Sammy.

6
00:04:47.078 --> 00:04:49.039
You really got those moves
locked down now, hmm?

7
00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:50.665
I sure do, Mr. Moon.

8
00:04:50.749 --> 00:04:53.376
Yeah, look at you.

9
00:04:53.502 --> 00:04:55.754
Great job, everybody. Great job.

10
00:04:55.837 --> 00:04:58.006
- Thanks, Mr. Moon.
- Yeah!

11
00:04:58.089 --> 00:05:00.258
I think we pretty much nailed it.

12
00:05:00.383 --> 00:05:01.383
So, is she here?

13
00:05:03.678 --> 00:05:06.014
There. See the dog, middle third row?

14
00:05:06.097 --> 00:05:07.933
Oh, she's younger
than I imagined.

15
00:05:08.016 --> 00:05:10.644
Well, supposedly,
she's the best scout in show business.

16
00:05:10.727 --> 00:05:12.687
I can't tell if... if she's enjoying it.

17
00:05:12.771 --> 00:05:14.189
Come on, let's get a better view.

18
00:05:28.078 --> 00:05:30.205
And how we doing over here, Miss Crawly?

19
00:05:30.288 --> 00:05:32.040
Oh, very good, Mr. Moon.

20
00:05:32.290 --> 00:05:34.751
So far, I counted nine smiles,

21
00:05:34.835 --> 00:05:37.504
two belly laughs and five chuckles.

22
00:05:37.587 --> 00:05:40.590
Uh, though the last one
could've just been gas.

23
00:05:40.757 --> 00:05:42.759
Well, that's proof, right?
She must like the show.

24
00:05:42.842 --> 00:05:44.553
- Oh, my gosh. You think so?
- I hope so.

25
00:05:44.636 --> 00:05:46.221
All right, now,
keep up the good work.

26
00:05:46.304 --> 00:05:47.931
Come on, everybody, back to positions.

27
00:05:48.014 --> 00:05:49.766
She'd be cuckoo
not to love this.

28
00:05:49.891 --> 00:05:52.519
Dream big dreams.

29
00:05:52.644 --> 00:05:54.187
That's what I always said, right?

30
00:05:54.312 --> 00:05:55.438
Mm-hmm.

31
00:05:55.522 --> 00:05:57.607
Well, looks like we're about
to take this show

32
00:05:57.691 --> 00:06:00.318
to the entertainment capital of the world.

33
00:06:00.443 --> 00:06:02.612
Mr. Moon, she's leaving.

34
00:06:02.737 --> 00:06:04.698
- Huh?
- She's leaving the show.

35
00:06:07.576 --> 00:06:09.536
Miss Crawly, stay right here.

36
00:06:09.661 --> 00:06:11.871
- What are you gonna do?
- I'm gonna follow that dog.

37
00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:18.795
Good heavens!

38
00:06:18.878 --> 00:06:20.463
- Hey, Nana.
- What are you doing?

39
00:06:20.547 --> 00:06:21.756
The scout is leaving.

40
00:06:23.174 --> 00:06:24.843
Ah, so she is.

41
00:06:25.343 --> 00:06:26.386
Hurry.

42
00:06:30.974 --> 00:06:32.809
Uh, Suki? Suki Lane?

43
00:06:33.059 --> 00:06:34.603
I'm Buster Moon.

44
00:06:34.686 --> 00:06:36.438
Uh, hi. So glad you could make it.

45
00:06:36.521 --> 00:06:37.772
Would you like some popcorn?

46
00:06:37.856 --> 00:06:40.775
Oh, no, thanks.
I'm not staying for the second half, so...

47
00:06:40.859 --> 00:06:42.611
Oh. But we thought
you were enjoying it.

48
00:06:42.694 --> 00:06:44.863
I mean, not that we were
watching you or anything.

49
00:06:44.946 --> 00:06:47.907
It really is a cute little show.

50
00:06:47.991 --> 00:06:49.492
Just not what we're looking for.

51
00:06:49.576 --> 00:06:51.620
But... but wait.
You got to see the second act.

52
00:06:51.703 --> 00:06:53.705
I'm... I'm telling you.
It's a smash.

53
00:06:53.788 --> 00:06:55.874
- Okay, Mr. Moon, can I be honest?
- Of course.

54
00:06:56.082 --> 00:06:58.793
Are you sure? 'Cause folks say that
when they don't mean it.

55
00:06:58.877 --> 00:07:00.962
No, please, please,
be as honest as you like.

56
00:07:01.046 --> 00:07:02.714
You're not good enough.

57
00:07:02.797 --> 00:07:04.007
What?

58
00:07:04.090 --> 00:07:05.508
Taxi!

59
00:07:05.592 --> 00:07:07.844
You know, maybe I will have that popcorn.

60
00:07:09.387 --> 00:07:12.098
Look, you've got a nice
little local theater here,

61
00:07:12.265 --> 00:07:14.351
and it's great for what it is,

62
00:07:14.476 --> 00:07:17.437
but trust me, you'd never make it
in the big leagues.

63
00:07:17.896 --> 00:07:18.980
Bye, now.

64
00:07:23.944 --> 00:07:26.529
Well, what did she say?

65
00:07:27.113 --> 00:07:28.198
I'll be right back.

66
00:07:29.074 --> 00:07:31.034
Nah. Mm-mm.

67
00:07:31.117 --> 00:07:33.078
A few laughs, bunch of quirky ideas.

68
00:07:33.203 --> 00:07:35.830
But, anyway, about Thursday...

69
00:07:36.373 --> 00:07:38.041
Oh, my...

70
00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:39.793
Yeah, hi. It's me again.

71
00:07:39.876 --> 00:07:41.836
Whoa.

72
00:07:42.003 --> 00:07:43.463
- Whoa.
- I'll call you back.

73
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:46.299
Are you out of your mind?

74
00:07:46.383 --> 00:07:47.717
When are you holding auditions?

75
00:07:47.842 --> 00:07:49.386
Tomorrow.

76
00:07:49.469 --> 00:07:51.054
- There's no way you...
- Listen...

77
00:07:51.179 --> 00:07:53.556
Get out of the road, you idiot!

78
00:07:53.682 --> 00:07:55.809
Hey, do you mind?
I'm in a meeting here.

79
00:07:55.934 --> 00:07:58.520
Could you at least give us a chance
to try out for your boss?

80
00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:00.981
Driver, could you please
lose this maniac?

81
00:08:01.064 --> 00:08:02.232
Wait. Hold on a second.

82
00:08:02.399 --> 00:08:03.650
No, no!

83
00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:15.513
Mr. Moon?

84
00:09:40.872 --> 00:09:42.665
Oh, for heaven's sake.

85
00:09:44.918 --> 00:09:46.586
What can I say, Nana?

86
00:09:46.669 --> 00:09:48.922
- I'm a failure.
- Oh, poppycock.

87
00:09:49.005 --> 00:09:50.423
I was reaching too high.

88
00:09:50.632 --> 00:09:54.677
Honestly, one negative comment,
and it's all, "Woe is me."

89
00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:57.055
Nana, come on.
She said I'm not good enough.

90
00:09:57.138 --> 00:10:00.058
I mean, heck,
I've just been told that my destiny,

91
00:10:00.141 --> 00:10:03.269
all of my hopes and dreams,
uh, they all end right here.

92
00:10:03.353 --> 00:10:04.687
Well, what did you expect?

93
00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:07.649
That she would drop to her knees
and declare you a genius?

94
00:10:07.732 --> 00:10:10.944
Roll out the red carpet
for the great Buster Moon!

95
00:10:11.152 --> 00:10:13.071
She... she ran me off the road
into a canal.

96
00:10:13.196 --> 00:10:15.740
- You're still in one piece, aren't you?
- Well, yeah, but...

97
00:10:15.907 --> 00:10:18.952
Well, anyone who dares set out
to follow their dreams

98
00:10:19.160 --> 00:10:22.664
is bound to face a lot worse
than a dip in the canal.

99
00:10:23.081 --> 00:10:24.624
Ah, Hobbs. I found him.

100
00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:26.459
Uh, bring the car round, will you?

101
00:10:26.543 --> 00:10:27.961
- There's a good chap.
- I... I...

102
00:10:28.044 --> 00:10:30.380
I just thought she'd at least
see we deserved a shot.

103
00:10:30.505 --> 00:10:33.216
Never mind what this person
you don't even know said.

104
00:10:33.299 --> 00:10:35.760
- Do you think you're good enough?
- Of course, but...

105
00:10:35.844 --> 00:10:37.887
Then you must fight
for what you believe in.

106
00:10:38.012 --> 00:10:40.390
Guts, stamina, faith.

107
00:10:40.473 --> 00:10:43.935
These are the things you need now,
and without them...

108
00:10:44.352 --> 00:10:46.563
Well, maybe that scout was right.

109
00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:49.274
Maybe you're not good enough.

110
00:11:33.318 --> 00:11:35.945
Oh, I... No, I know, Rosita,
but trust me on this.

111
00:11:36.029 --> 00:11:37.405
It'll be totally worth it.

112
00:11:37.488 --> 00:11:39.240
And listen,
I'm outside her place now,

113
00:11:39.365 --> 00:11:41.910
can you call the others
and have 'em meet in half an hour?

114
00:11:42.285 --> 00:11:43.620
Great. Thank you.

115
00:12:18.154 --> 00:12:19.530
Thank you so much.

116
00:12:19.948 --> 00:12:20.948
Good night.

117
00:12:24.077 --> 00:12:25.244
Moon. Hey.

118
00:12:26.996 --> 00:12:28.998
Wow.
You were great out there.

119
00:12:29.082 --> 00:12:31.000
- I got to go back out for an encore.
- Okay.

120
00:12:31.084 --> 00:12:33.294
- What are you doing after the show?
- Uh, nothing.

121
00:12:33.503 --> 00:12:35.380
Listen, I know this is
crazy short notice,

122
00:12:35.463 --> 00:12:37.298
but you always said
you'd come back to us

123
00:12:37.423 --> 00:12:38.943
- when the time was right.
- Of course.

124
00:12:39.092 --> 00:12:41.469
Well, this is that time.

125
00:12:41.594 --> 00:12:42.971
Here, paycheck.

126
00:12:43.054 --> 00:12:44.973
I'm getting the gang together
to go audition

127
00:12:45.056 --> 00:12:46.936
- for this huge show...
- Just... just a second.

128
00:12:46.975 --> 00:12:49.185
Hey, Rick, how come
you're only paying me

129
00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:50.561
half what the other acts get?

130
00:12:50.728 --> 00:12:52.772
- I pay what I think you're worth.
- Oh, okay.

131
00:12:53.314 --> 00:12:58.194
See, I have this rule about not letting
guys like you tell me what I'm worth,

132
00:12:58.277 --> 00:13:01.781
so, you know, unless I get paid
like everyone else, I'm out of here.

133
00:13:01.864 --> 00:13:03.825
This is the only club in town.

134
00:13:03.908 --> 00:13:05.076
Where else you gonna play?

135
00:13:05.159 --> 00:13:08.621
I have no idea, but I'm sure as heck
not sticking around here.

136
00:13:08.746 --> 00:13:09.831
Let's go.

137
00:13:09.914 --> 00:13:10.957
Ooh!

138
00:13:11.165 --> 00:13:14.168
Whoa, whoa. Wait a minute.
You... you got to do the encore.

139
00:13:14.293 --> 00:13:15.670
Hey, Ash!

140
00:13:15.753 --> 00:13:17.338
Deal with it, sweetheart.

141
00:13:18.214 --> 00:13:20.425
<i>Redshore City Bus five</i>

142
00:13:20.550 --> 00:13:22.760
<i>leaving from park 15...</i>

143
00:13:22.885 --> 00:13:24.595
Okay, I got the tickets.

144
00:13:24.804 --> 00:13:26.973
Anyone seen Miss Crawly?
Here you go, Johnny.

145
00:13:27.056 --> 00:13:28.367
- Here's yours, and...
- Mr. Moon.

146
00:13:28.391 --> 00:13:32.311
Uh, uh, I'm sorry, but I'm really having
second thoughts about this.

147
00:13:32.729 --> 00:13:34.439
What? No, no, no, wait.

148
00:13:34.605 --> 00:13:36.399
All right, last call. Let's go.

149
00:13:36.482 --> 00:13:38.401
- Now, just a second.
- Johnny's right.

150
00:13:38.609 --> 00:13:41.946
I mean, that theater scout,
she didn't think we were good enough.

151
00:13:42.071 --> 00:13:44.032
- She sounds like a jerk.
- Yeah, total jerk.

152
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:46.367
Yeah, but she's wrong... Dead wrong.

153
00:13:46.451 --> 00:13:49.078
There's a reason our show
is sold out every night,

154
00:13:49.412 --> 00:13:51.581
and I'm telling you,
her boss is gonna love it.

155
00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:55.168
Ooh. Or maybe we could just, like,
do a different show, you know?

156
00:13:55.251 --> 00:13:56.711
Gunter, please, I got this.

157
00:13:56.794 --> 00:14:00.048
Seriously, I have this idea
for, like, a space musical.

158
00:14:00.131 --> 00:14:02.800
All right, we're rolling out here.

159
00:14:02.967 --> 00:14:05.344
You don't want to hear
about the space musical?

160
00:14:05.428 --> 00:14:07.513
Guys, come on!

161
00:14:07.889 --> 00:14:09.098
Wait!

162
00:14:17.523 --> 00:14:19.067
Listen, you guys,

163
00:14:19.275 --> 00:14:23.905
I have dreamt of performing
in Redshore City since I was a little kid.

164
00:14:23.988 --> 00:14:26.157
And besides,
I just convinced my husband

165
00:14:26.282 --> 00:14:28.201
to babysit for the next 24 hours,

166
00:14:28.326 --> 00:14:31.079
and I am not gonna waste
an opportunity like that.

167
00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:33.706
So come on.
We've got nothing to lose.

168
00:14:36.542 --> 00:14:38.836
Here, Ash.
You come in on page two.

169
00:14:38.920 --> 00:14:40.671
Wait. We're just gonna
rehearse this here

170
00:14:40.755 --> 00:14:42.632
- at the back of the bus?
- We are.

171
00:14:42.757 --> 00:14:44.759
- Course we are.
- Yep.

172
00:14:44.884 --> 00:14:47.011
We got to get this show
in the best shape ever.

173
00:14:47.136 --> 00:14:48.805
Ah, Miss Crawly, you made it. Good.

174
00:14:49.013 --> 00:14:51.557
You are an angel, and we're
sure gonna need that...

175
00:14:51.641 --> 00:14:52.850
Whoa!

176
00:14:53.017 --> 00:14:54.102
What the...

177
00:14:54.477 --> 00:14:58.523
Uh, well, you did say, "Dress to impress."

178
00:15:53.828 --> 00:15:57.206
Let's cut that and have you play
the guitar part through the whole scene.

179
00:15:57.290 --> 00:15:59.959
- Got it.
- Guys, we're here.

180
00:16:29.697 --> 00:16:33.284
All right. Let's go spread
a little Moon Theater magic.

181
00:16:34.827 --> 00:16:36.204
- Woo-hoo!
- Come on!

182
00:16:39.874 --> 00:16:40.875
No.

183
00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:42.543
No? What do you mean, "no"?

184
00:16:42.627 --> 00:16:45.421
For the last time, sir,
no appointment, no entry.

185
00:16:45.505 --> 00:16:47.173
- Um...
- Sir, do I need to call security?

186
00:16:47.256 --> 00:16:49.050
- We should go.
- You should.

187
00:16:49.133 --> 00:16:50.259
Next.

188
00:16:50.343 --> 00:16:53.346
- I don't like this.
- How may I help you?

189
00:16:53.429 --> 00:16:54.764
I'm here to see Mr. Crystal...

190
00:16:54.847 --> 00:16:55.973
This is so unfair.

191
00:16:56.057 --> 00:16:58.351
She's, like, totally unfair, that lady.

192
00:16:58.434 --> 00:17:00.811
I mean, why's she got
to be so snotty about it?

193
00:17:00.895 --> 00:17:02.897
I got all dressed up for nothing.

194
00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:05.274
Let's find somewhere
for lunch and hang out.

195
00:17:05.358 --> 00:17:07.860
In here. Quick. Get in.

196
00:17:10.780 --> 00:17:11.780
Hmm.

197
00:17:11.864 --> 00:17:13.032
- Come on.
- So dark in here.

198
00:17:13.115 --> 00:17:14.909
- What's going on?
- I got to think.

199
00:17:15.076 --> 00:17:17.370
Mr. Moon? I'm not so good in small spaces.

200
00:17:17.662 --> 00:17:20.122
- Okay, okay.
- Ow! Somebody stepped on my trotter.

201
00:17:20.206 --> 00:17:21.374
- Sorry.
- Honey. Come on.

202
00:17:21.457 --> 00:17:23.501
- Let's get you out of here.
- Aha!

203
00:17:23.584 --> 00:17:24.752
Look at this.

204
00:17:24.835 --> 00:17:25.920
Meena.

205
00:17:26.003 --> 00:17:27.964
Do you think that's kind of your size?

206
00:17:47.733 --> 00:17:48.776
Hey, Ricky.

207
00:17:49.485 --> 00:17:52.196
Hi.

208
00:17:58.828 --> 00:18:00.204
Crystal Entertainment.

209
00:18:00.288 --> 00:18:02.248
- Uh, hold one moment, sir.
- Phew.

210
00:18:02.331 --> 00:18:04.166
- I'll... I'll connect you.
- Oh, no.

211
00:18:04.250 --> 00:18:06.544
- No, no, no, no, no.
- Everybody, hold on.

212
00:18:09.463 --> 00:18:11.382
- Mr. Moon?
- Hold tight, Miss Crawly.

213
00:18:23.603 --> 00:18:24.645
Good job.

214
00:18:24.729 --> 00:18:26.480
Now, into the elevator.

215
00:18:26.564 --> 00:18:28.149
Quick. Go, go, go, go.

216
00:18:29.025 --> 00:18:30.151
Meena! Come on!

217
00:18:36.782 --> 00:18:38.909
We could all get arrested for...

218
00:18:57.887 --> 00:18:59.388
Everybody, mop.

219
00:19:08.356 --> 00:19:10.358
Uh...

220
00:19:36.967 --> 00:19:38.177
Where are you going now?

221
00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:40.888
I'm gonna find somewhere to change
out of this stuff.

222
00:19:42.848 --> 00:19:43.848
Ah.

223
00:20:12.545 --> 00:20:14.171
Look, that's him.

224
00:20:14.255 --> 00:20:16.298
That is the Mr. Crystal.

225
00:20:17.967 --> 00:20:19.593
Garbage.

226
00:21:55.481 --> 00:21:57.233
Okay, everybody,

227
00:21:57.316 --> 00:21:59.902
if you can leave immediately,
single file,

228
00:21:59.985 --> 00:22:01.862
we'd appreciate that.

229
00:22:01.946 --> 00:22:03.239
Thank you very much.

230
00:22:03.656 --> 00:22:05.157
Jerry, for the love of...

231
00:22:05.241 --> 00:22:07.368
- Sorry, sir.
- Where's the next group?

232
00:22:07.451 --> 00:22:10.329
- Why am I standing here waiting?
- How about I just...

233
00:22:10.412 --> 00:22:12.873
- Be useful or be gone, okay?
- Yes. Yes, sir. Yes, sir.

234
00:22:12.957 --> 00:22:14.708
Um, okay. Um, you.

235
00:22:15.334 --> 00:22:18.462
Hey. Hey. Yeah, you.
Little guy, you're here for the audition?

236
00:22:18.587 --> 00:22:20.172
Uh, yes.

237
00:22:20.256 --> 00:22:22.007
Yeah, yeah, yes, we are.

238
00:22:22.258 --> 00:22:23.843
Guys, we're on right now.

239
00:22:23.968 --> 00:22:24.969
- Now?
- What?

240
00:22:27.555 --> 00:22:29.431
Your name? Your name, please?

241
00:22:30.057 --> 00:22:32.393
<i>Uh, it's Buster Moon
from the New Moon Theater.</i>

242
00:22:32.518 --> 00:22:36.021
<i>And we're very excited to share
our story with you today. Right, guys?</i>

243
00:22:36.230 --> 00:22:37.898
Yeah, great. Now, get to it.

244
00:22:37.982 --> 00:22:38.983
<i>Of course. Yes.</i>

245
00:22:39.066 --> 00:22:40.484
Guys, just like we rehearsed.

246
00:22:44.405 --> 00:22:45.573
<i>This is the story</i>

247
00:22:45.656 --> 00:22:47.950
<i>of an ordinary high school girl
who discovers...</i>

248
00:22:48.367 --> 00:22:49.660
Stop.

249
00:22:49.743 --> 00:22:51.412
<i>- Stop?</i>
- He wants you to stop.

250
00:22:52.621 --> 00:22:54.623
"Ordinary" and "school."

251
00:22:54.707 --> 00:22:56.667
Two words I will never
be associated with.

252
00:22:56.750 --> 00:22:58.127
- Never.
- Where the heck did you

253
00:22:58.210 --> 00:22:59.336
dig these guys up from?

254
00:22:59.420 --> 00:23:01.964
If you could all leave quickly,
we'd appreciate that.

255
00:23:02.047 --> 00:23:03.632
I need big shows, Jerry.

256
00:23:03.716 --> 00:23:05.759
- Big ideas!
- Yes, sir, big. The biggest.

257
00:23:05.843 --> 00:23:07.636
Hey, I have a big one.

258
00:23:09.179 --> 00:23:11.056
Okay, honey. Come on, let's go.

259
00:23:11.140 --> 00:23:12.558
You know, the sci-fi musical.

260
00:23:12.641 --> 00:23:14.018
- That's big, right?
- Um, uh...

261
00:23:14.101 --> 00:23:16.895
I mean, it's got
the aliens and the robots

262
00:23:16.979 --> 00:23:19.607
and the lasers
and these amazing songs

263
00:23:19.690 --> 00:23:21.275
from, like, Clay Calloway to...

264
00:23:21.358 --> 00:23:23.736
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Clay Calloway?

265
00:23:23.861 --> 00:23:25.446
I love Clay Calloway.

266
00:23:25.946 --> 00:23:28.657
<i>I know, right?
I mean, doesn't everybody?</i>

267
00:23:28.741 --> 00:23:30.075
Yeah. See, Jerry?

268
00:23:30.159 --> 00:23:33.412
This is exactly the kind
of big idea I'm talking about.

269
00:23:33.495 --> 00:23:35.080
- Yes, sir.
- So, uh...

270
00:23:35.164 --> 00:23:36.415
so what's the show called?

271
00:23:36.498 --> 00:23:38.792
<i>What's it called? Um...</i>

272
00:23:38.876 --> 00:23:41.045
<i>- Gunter, you, uh...
- you want to...</i>

273
00:23:41.128 --> 00:23:42.755
<i>tell Mr. Crystal what it's called?</i>

274
00:23:42.838 --> 00:23:45.883
Uh-huh. It's called
<i>Out of This World.</i>

275
00:23:46.258 --> 00:23:49.303
<i>Out of This World.</i>

276
00:23:49.386 --> 00:23:51.597
<i>That's right. Just imagine it.</i>

277
00:23:52.264 --> 00:23:53.098
Ash?

278
00:23:53.182 --> 00:23:55.184
Uh, yeah, I got it.

279
00:23:56.393 --> 00:24:01.482
<i>A spectacular musical that takes
your audience out of this world.</i>

280
00:24:15.287 --> 00:24:16.705
I love this song.

281
00:24:30.177 --> 00:24:33.389
Sir, your lunch meeting with...
Oh, my...

282
00:24:33.514 --> 00:24:34.640
Not now.

283
00:24:34.723 --> 00:24:36.141
Moon, how did you get in here?

284
00:24:36.225 --> 00:24:37.225
He said not now. Psst.

285
00:24:37.267 --> 00:24:39.019
Yeah, I heard him. Thanks, Jerry.

286
00:24:39.103 --> 00:24:42.648
Are you telling me you got Clay Calloway's
permission to use his song?

287
00:24:42.898 --> 00:24:45.234
- Well, what if I told you I did?
- Ah.

288
00:24:45.317 --> 00:24:48.320
So what, you got some kind of
personal connection to this guy?

289
00:24:48.445 --> 00:24:50.531
- How else would I get it?
- Moon!

290
00:24:50.614 --> 00:24:52.116
Wait, if you know him,

291
00:24:52.199 --> 00:24:55.703
then you could get him
in the show, right?

292
00:24:56.620 --> 00:25:00.332
Oh, that'd be huge for me. Huge.

293
00:25:00.833 --> 00:25:02.376
Sir, I'm sorry, but seriously?

294
00:25:02.459 --> 00:25:07.464
You think this little guy from nowhere
can get Clay Calloway in the show?

295
00:25:09.383 --> 00:25:11.593
Well, Suki, for your information,

296
00:25:11.677 --> 00:25:14.471
I am not just a little guy from nowhere.

297
00:25:15.264 --> 00:25:16.765
Consider it done, sir.

298
00:25:17.057 --> 00:25:18.976
I'll give you three weeks, Moon.

299
00:25:19.059 --> 00:25:21.145
Three weeks to get this show
up and running.

300
00:25:21.228 --> 00:25:22.771
Yes, sir. Thank you.

301
00:25:22.855 --> 00:25:25.441
- Do you really know Clay Calloway?
- Shh. Not now.

302
00:25:25.607 --> 00:25:27.151
- Jerry.
- Oh! Right here, sir.

303
00:25:27.276 --> 00:25:29.737
I want these guys
to start work now.

304
00:25:29.820 --> 00:25:32.740
Set 'em up with our designers,
our dancers, whatever they need.

305
00:25:32.865 --> 00:25:34.491
And get 'em rooms at the hotel, okay?

306
00:25:34.575 --> 00:25:36.785
The very best suites.
The whole shaboodle.

307
00:25:36.869 --> 00:25:37.869
Yes, of course.

308
00:25:38.078 --> 00:25:39.413
Uh, hey, one last thing.

309
00:25:39.496 --> 00:25:42.666
Don't you ever do nothing
to make me look bad. You got that?

310
00:25:42.750 --> 00:25:44.501
I will never let that happen, sir.

311
00:25:44.585 --> 00:25:46.587
You better not,
or I'll throw you off the roof.

312
00:25:48.881 --> 00:25:50.090
Great job, everyone.

313
00:25:50.215 --> 00:25:51.759
Take it away, Raoul.

314
00:25:57.389 --> 00:25:58.474
Oh, my gosh.

315
00:25:58.599 --> 00:26:00.142
- Is this really happening?
- Yeah!

316
00:26:00.225 --> 00:26:02.644
We're playing Redshore City, baby!

317
00:26:02.728 --> 00:26:05.105
Yes, we are, Gunter.

318
00:26:05.355 --> 00:26:08.484
Gunter, sci-fi musical? You're a genius.

319
00:26:08.692 --> 00:26:10.611
Yeah, well, Mama always said,

320
00:26:10.694 --> 00:26:13.572
"Gunter, you're not as stupid
as your papa."

321
00:26:13.655 --> 00:26:15.199
No, you're not.

322
00:26:15.282 --> 00:26:16.867
Hey, Suki.

323
00:26:16.950 --> 00:26:18.160
No hard feelings, huh?

324
00:26:18.243 --> 00:26:20.829
You have no idea
what you're getting into.

325
00:26:20.913 --> 00:26:21.913
Whoa.

326
00:26:21.997 --> 00:26:23.349
- Are you out of your mind?
- What?

327
00:26:23.373 --> 00:26:25.626
Clay Calloway?
I'm, like, his biggest fan,

328
00:26:25.709 --> 00:26:27.920
and I can tell you, the guy is a recluse.

329
00:26:28.003 --> 00:26:31.840
Seriously, after his wife died,
no one's seen him in over 15 years.

330
00:26:31.924 --> 00:26:34.051
Ah. That's not good.

331
00:26:34.134 --> 00:26:35.803
No, it's not.

332
00:26:36.053 --> 00:26:37.221
Uh...

333
00:26:37.387 --> 00:26:40.098
Miss Crawly, I need you
to help me find Clay Calloway.

334
00:26:40.182 --> 00:26:41.809
An address, a phone number, anything.

335
00:26:41.892 --> 00:26:43.852
- But we've got to find that guy.
- Yes, sir.

336
00:26:45.479 --> 00:26:46.355
<i>Good morning!</i>

337
00:26:46.438 --> 00:26:49.483
<i>I'm Linda Le Bon,
and have I got some hot news for you.</i>

338
00:26:51.610 --> 00:26:54.071
<i>Infamous billionaire
Jimmy Crystal has hired</i>

339
00:26:54.154 --> 00:26:55.781
<i>- an unknown theater producer...</i>
- What?

340
00:26:55.906 --> 00:26:58.200
<i>By the name of Buster Moon.</i>

341
00:27:46.623 --> 00:27:49.042
Okay, so this guy
is coming in from that side,

342
00:27:49.126 --> 00:27:50.919
and it's, like, cuckoo crazy,

343
00:27:51.003 --> 00:27:54.882
and then I think we should have, like,
this cool alien tango scene.

344
00:27:55.215 --> 00:27:59.344
"Alien tango scene."

345
00:27:59.511 --> 00:28:01.096
Oh. I love it.

346
00:28:01.179 --> 00:28:02.890
Wait. I've got a better idea.

347
00:28:02.973 --> 00:28:06.602
What if it was, like,
a big underwater scene instead?

348
00:28:07.019 --> 00:28:08.270
- Underwater?
- Yeah, yeah.

349
00:28:08.353 --> 00:28:09.646
I'm sure of this. Write it down.

350
00:28:09.730 --> 00:28:11.690
- Mm, okay.
- Wait, wait.

351
00:28:11.773 --> 00:28:14.318
Stop your clicky-clacky.
I have a better idea.

352
00:28:14.401 --> 00:28:16.820
- Uh, you can't keep changing your mind.
- Why?

353
00:28:16.987 --> 00:28:19.072
Why? Because in exactly 20 minutes,

354
00:28:19.156 --> 00:28:22.284
the stage crew are coming here
to start work on our show,

355
00:28:22.367 --> 00:28:24.578
and we need to lock this stuff down.

356
00:28:24.661 --> 00:28:26.747
My gosh, they're early.

357
00:28:26.830 --> 00:28:29.666
Ooh, and I want to have, like,
this beautiful love scene...

358
00:28:29.791 --> 00:28:31.585
Miss Crawly,
anything on Calloway?

359
00:28:31.668 --> 00:28:33.587
- Hmm, not a thing.
- Oh, geez.

360
00:28:36.548 --> 00:28:37.633
Ah, Mr. Moon.

361
00:28:37.716 --> 00:28:40.093
We're your production team,
and we're here to start...

362
00:28:40.219 --> 00:28:42.721
Yes, yes, yes.
Uh, you're here to work on the show.

363
00:28:42.804 --> 00:28:45.140
And I would gladly invite
you all in right now, but...

364
00:28:45.224 --> 00:28:47.392
We should totally do,
like, a battle scene!

365
00:28:47.476 --> 00:28:49.519
Gunter, no, not now.

366
00:28:49.603 --> 00:28:51.521
I just need a little more time
to, you know,

367
00:28:51.688 --> 00:28:53.357
hammer out a few minor, little details,

368
00:28:53.440 --> 00:28:56.068
so would it be okay
if you all could come back in, like,

369
00:28:56.151 --> 00:28:58.237
I don't know, an hour?
Or maybe four?

370
00:28:58.320 --> 00:29:00.322
And I really appreciate your patience.

371
00:29:00.405 --> 00:29:01.698
Thank you so much.

372
00:29:02.032 --> 00:29:03.659
Hmm. Okay.

373
00:29:04.159 --> 00:29:06.453
Okay.
That was not a great start.

374
00:29:06.536 --> 00:29:09.456
- Oh, look, it's a gift from Mr. Crystal.
- Huh.

375
00:29:09.581 --> 00:29:11.416
It... it says, um,

376
00:29:11.625 --> 00:29:14.127
"Don't screw up, Moon, or else."

377
00:29:14.461 --> 00:29:16.213
Ooh, I've got a better idea.

378
00:29:27.140 --> 00:29:28.642
Good morning.

379
00:29:28.725 --> 00:29:30.936
May I have everyone's attention, please?

380
00:29:31.520 --> 00:29:33.397
Thank you. Yes.

381
00:29:33.814 --> 00:29:36.775
Okay, um, on behalf
of myself and the cast,

382
00:29:36.858 --> 00:29:40.028
I just want to say that to be given
this incredible opportunity

383
00:29:40.153 --> 00:29:42.572
to work with you all here
at the Crystal Tower Theater,

384
00:29:42.656 --> 00:29:44.491
well, it's an honor for all of us.

385
00:29:44.574 --> 00:29:45.826
And I believe that, together,

386
00:29:45.909 --> 00:29:48.745
we can make a show that'll take
the audience out of this world.

387
00:29:51.415 --> 00:29:53.292
And a big thanks to Steve over here

388
00:29:53.500 --> 00:29:55.460
for staying up all night
to make this model.

389
00:29:55.544 --> 00:29:56.712
Great work, Steve.

390
00:29:56.878 --> 00:29:58.714
And here she is, folks.

391
00:29:58.797 --> 00:30:01.383
The star of our show, Rosita.

392
00:30:01.466 --> 00:30:04.177
That's you, baby!

393
00:30:04.261 --> 00:30:05.387
The lead role?

394
00:30:05.470 --> 00:30:07.556
Trust me, you are perfect for it.

395
00:30:09.391 --> 00:30:11.310
Wait till my kids hear about this.

396
00:30:11.393 --> 00:30:13.478
And so the story goes like this.

397
00:30:13.562 --> 00:30:17.524
Rosita plays an astronaut
searching for a missing space explorer.

398
00:30:17.607 --> 00:30:19.318
Together, with their trusty robot...

399
00:30:19.443 --> 00:30:21.069
- That's me.
- Mm-hm, yes.

400
00:30:21.153 --> 00:30:23.363
They follow the trail across four planets.

401
00:30:23.447 --> 00:30:26.325
There's a planet of war, a planet of love,

402
00:30:26.408 --> 00:30:28.493
a one of despair and one of joy.

403
00:30:28.577 --> 00:30:31.663
And each planet will have its own
spectacular musical number

404
00:30:31.747 --> 00:30:33.665
performed by one of our terrific cast.

405
00:30:34.791 --> 00:30:36.793
And how does it end?
Do I find the explorer?

406
00:30:36.877 --> 00:30:39.338
We have no clue what
we're going to do at the end.

407
00:30:39.421 --> 00:30:41.089
Gunter, no, no, no. Whoa.

408
00:30:41.173 --> 00:30:43.425
We do have great ideas for the ending.

409
00:30:43.508 --> 00:30:44.968
We just... All right.

410
00:30:45.052 --> 00:30:47.346
We've only got three weeks
to make this reality.

411
00:30:47.429 --> 00:30:48.429
Let's get to work.

412
00:30:48.722 --> 00:30:51.391
Johnny, you are gonna play
an alien warrior

413
00:30:51.475 --> 00:30:52.934
in a fantastic battle scene.

414
00:30:53.143 --> 00:30:54.978
- Yes!
- Come with me.

415
00:31:02.527 --> 00:31:04.863
Johnny, I want you to meet
your fellow dancers.

416
00:31:04.946 --> 00:31:06.782
- Hello, lads.
- Hey, how you doing?

417
00:31:06.865 --> 00:31:08.867
Uh, wait.
You said mine was a battle scene.

418
00:31:08.950 --> 00:31:12.204
Well, it is, but Gunter saw it
as more of a... a dance battle.

419
00:31:12.287 --> 00:31:14.247
- Yeah!
- Okay...

420
00:31:14.331 --> 00:31:16.166
Johnny, don't worry.
You're gonna be working

421
00:31:16.249 --> 00:31:19.002
with the number one choreographer
in Redshore City.

422
00:31:19.086 --> 00:31:21.213
"Klaus Kickenklober."

423
00:31:21.380 --> 00:31:23.382
Yep. Klaus will turn you
into a pro in no time.

424
00:31:23.465 --> 00:31:24.508
Okay.

425
00:31:24.591 --> 00:31:26.134
- Uh...
- Mr. Moon?

426
00:31:26.927 --> 00:31:28.428
Meena, you okay?

427
00:31:28.720 --> 00:31:32.682
Gunter said I'm in a romantic scene
and, uh, uh...

428
00:31:32.766 --> 00:31:34.393
I have to kiss someone.

429
00:31:34.643 --> 00:31:37.813
Yeah. It's gonna be an amazing,
beautiful, romantic scene.

430
00:31:37.938 --> 00:31:41.358
Mr. Moon, I've never even had
a boyfriend or any of that stuff.

431
00:31:41.608 --> 00:31:42.651
Ah, don't you worry.

432
00:31:42.818 --> 00:31:45.195
I'm gonna cast a great partner for you.

433
00:31:45.278 --> 00:31:46.738
- Promise?
- Promise.

434
00:31:46.947 --> 00:31:50.409
Mr. Moon, we're ready to start building
the rest of the sets and...

435
00:31:50.492 --> 00:31:51.827
Okay, okay, okay, listen.

436
00:31:51.910 --> 00:31:53.995
I don't exactly know
what they are yet,

437
00:31:54.121 --> 00:31:56.581
so could you give me one more
night to figure this out?

438
00:31:56.665 --> 00:31:59.042
Hey, this guy
doesn't have it figured out,

439
00:31:59.126 --> 00:32:01.545
- so we can't start work right now.
- Mason?

440
00:32:01.628 --> 00:32:03.268
- Did everybody hear that?
- Hey, don't...

441
00:32:03.338 --> 00:32:04.923
He does not have the show
figured out.

442
00:32:05.006 --> 00:32:07.676
I'm looking into his eyes,

443
00:32:07.759 --> 00:32:09.845
- and all I see is fear.
- Uh-uh. Mm-mm.

444
00:32:09.928 --> 00:32:12.055
- Hey, listen. Yeah.
- And a little bit of shame.

445
00:32:12.139 --> 00:32:14.724
Look, I think everyone heard you, Mason.
Thank you so much.

446
00:32:14.808 --> 00:32:16.810
Gunter...
We have work to do.

447
00:32:16.893 --> 00:32:19.729
And then I'm thinking,
Ash, you know, she can, like,

448
00:32:19.813 --> 00:32:22.065
totally have a duet
with Clay Calloway,

449
00:32:22.149 --> 00:32:24.985
'cause, like, she's a star
that is, like,

450
00:32:25.068 --> 00:32:27.362
guiding them all the way
back home again.

451
00:32:27.446 --> 00:32:29.906
Yes, Gunter.
That's perfect for Ash.

452
00:32:30.949 --> 00:32:33.243
Mommy!

453
00:32:33.535 --> 00:32:35.495
Oh, my darlings, you're here.

454
00:32:35.579 --> 00:32:36.913
Yeah, Johnny!

455
00:32:36.997 --> 00:32:38.373
Oh.

456
00:32:38.457 --> 00:32:40.834
I wasn't expecting you till the morning.

457
00:32:40.917 --> 00:32:43.128
I know, but they couldn't wait to see you.

458
00:32:43.378 --> 00:32:45.088
The star of the show, huh?

459
00:32:45.172 --> 00:32:48.091
Can you believe it?
It's literally my dream come true.

460
00:32:48.216 --> 00:32:50.260
- I know. Mwah.
- Ew.

461
00:32:50.343 --> 00:32:52.262
I am so proud of you, honey.

462
00:32:54.139 --> 00:32:55.432
Uh... help.

463
00:32:55.515 --> 00:32:57.809
Mr. Moon, I found him.

464
00:32:57.934 --> 00:33:00.479
- Clay Calloway?
- Yeah. I found his home address.

465
00:33:00.562 --> 00:33:02.230
No way.

466
00:33:02.314 --> 00:33:03.398
Yes way.

467
00:33:03.482 --> 00:33:06.693
Miss Crawly, I'm gonna need you
to go visit him first thing tomorrow.

468
00:33:06.776 --> 00:33:08.653
- Yes, sir.
- You'll need to rent a car

469
00:33:08.737 --> 00:33:11.031
and take him a letter
and maybe that fruit basket.

470
00:33:11.156 --> 00:33:13.575
- Yes, the fruit basket. You got that?
- Got it.

471
00:33:13.700 --> 00:33:16.953
And one, two, three, four,

472
00:33:17.370 --> 00:33:19.247
five, six, seven, eight.

473
00:33:19.331 --> 00:33:21.249
We're dancing. We're dancing.

474
00:33:21.333 --> 00:33:23.335
We're holding. We're holding.

475
00:33:23.418 --> 00:33:24.503
Stay <i>en pointe.</i>

476
00:33:24.586 --> 00:33:26.796
Shuffle and hold.

477
00:33:26.922 --> 00:33:29.257
I said hold, Johnny.
He's not holding.

478
00:33:29.674 --> 00:33:32.260
- And one, two, three, four...
- All right, I am trying.

479
00:33:32.344 --> 00:33:37.140
Let's not forget, this is Redshore City,
not your little local theater.

480
00:33:37.224 --> 00:33:39.309
And five, six, seven, eight.

481
00:33:39.392 --> 00:33:41.269
Ryan, that was excellent.

482
00:33:41.436 --> 00:33:43.438
Johnny, you are doing it wrong.

483
00:33:43.688 --> 00:33:44.856
That was awful.

484
00:33:44.940 --> 00:33:46.233
Johnny. You can do better.

485
00:33:46.316 --> 00:33:48.276
- He's freaking me out.
- Johnny.

486
00:33:48.360 --> 00:33:49.778
- I'm trying.
- Thrust.

487
00:33:49.861 --> 00:33:51.404
And thrust, and thrust.

488
00:33:51.488 --> 00:33:52.864
You're not thrusting, Johnny.

489
00:33:52.948 --> 00:33:54.324
- Come on. Thrust.
- Thrust.

490
00:33:54.449 --> 00:33:56.618
Still not thrusting.
Can you thrust, please?

491
00:33:56.701 --> 00:34:00.580
Five, six, seven,
and tippy-toes, tippy-toes.

492
00:34:00.664 --> 00:34:02.457
I don't see your tippy-toes.

493
00:34:02.541 --> 00:34:04.042
Come on, he's having a laugh.

