623
00:42:32.175 --> 00:42:33.426
You get me?

624
00:42:33.760 --> 00:42:35.011
- Uh...
- What?

625
00:42:35.094 --> 00:42:37.597
You don't think my daughter's
good enough for your show?

626
00:42:37.680 --> 00:42:40.058
No, Mr. Crystal.
Well, I think she's wonderful.

627
00:42:40.183 --> 00:42:41.934
Oh, good. So you'll figure it out.

628
00:42:42.018 --> 00:42:43.686
I'll... Yes, I will.

629
00:42:44.020 --> 00:42:46.814
- Daddy, I'm hungry for French toast.
- Jerry!

630
00:42:46.898 --> 00:42:48.566
- Yes, sir.
- Get her some of that.

631
00:42:48.691 --> 00:42:50.276
And, by the way, I like the set.

632
00:42:50.359 --> 00:42:52.320
That whole
"rings moving around" thing.

633
00:42:52.403 --> 00:42:54.197
Creative, quirky. I like it.

634
00:42:54.280 --> 00:42:55.865
Bye, Daddy.

635
00:42:55.948 --> 00:42:59.160
Mm-kay. Let's have Porsha measured
for a costume right away, please.

636
00:42:59.243 --> 00:43:00.078
Right away.

637
00:43:00.161 --> 00:43:02.288
Would you just get
the French toast, Jerry?

638
00:43:02.371 --> 00:43:03.873
I'm getting the French toast.

639
00:43:03.956 --> 00:43:04.874
You okay?

640
00:43:04.957 --> 00:43:07.335
A little shaky, but I'm okay.

641
00:43:07.418 --> 00:43:09.253
Yeah. You know, uh...

642
00:43:09.337 --> 00:43:11.422
Look, maybe this is for the best, huh?

643
00:43:11.506 --> 00:43:14.967
- I mean, you really were scared up there.
- Right.

644
00:43:15.051 --> 00:43:16.886
I'll write you another part, Rosita.

645
00:43:16.969 --> 00:43:19.138
A really... a really, really great part.

646
00:43:19.222 --> 00:43:21.182
- You all right?
- Oh, I'm fine.

647
00:43:21.265 --> 00:43:23.101
- Really?
- Yes, you're all very sweet,

648
00:43:23.184 --> 00:43:26.187
