01:04:09.304 --> 01:04:14.100
Porsha, you know I truly believe
that this show, it...

996
01:04:14.184 --> 01:04:16.770
it's close to being fantastic,
maybe even perfect.

997
01:04:16.936 --> 01:04:18.646
- Thank you.
- Yeah, yeah,

998
01:04:18.855 --> 01:04:21.649
but... but, see, to make it
the best it can be...

999
01:04:22.942 --> 01:04:25.320
well, I got to make some changes.

1000
01:04:25.695 --> 01:04:26.946
Uh-huh.

1001
01:04:27.280 --> 01:04:28.448
Like...

1002
01:04:30.533 --> 01:04:32.827
I have to give the lead role
back to Rosita.

1003
01:04:32.994 --> 01:04:33.870
What?

1004
01:04:33.953 --> 01:04:36.331
I'm just offering you the opportunity

1005
01:04:36.456 --> 01:04:38.458
- to switch roles with...
- You're firing me?

1006
01:04:38.583 --> 01:04:39.876
No, I... I'm not firing you.

1007
01:04:39.959 --> 01:04:42.170
Oh, wait till my dad hears
that you fired me.

1008
01:04:42.253 --> 01:04:44.422
But I'm not firing you. Please, wait!

1009
01:04:45.131 --> 01:04:47.467
Oh, my gosh.

1010
01:04:47.550 --> 01:04:49.135
You all hate me, don't you?

1011
01:04:49.427 --> 01:04:52.472
No, no, no, we don't hate you.
We all think you're terrific!

1012
01:04:52.555 --> 01:04:54.682
- Well, I don't care if you hate me.
- Please stop.

1013
01:04:54.766 --> 01:04:58.520
You and your stupid,
stupid sky-fi show

1014
01:04:58.645 --> 01:04:59.813
can go to heck!

1015
01:04:59.896 --> 01:05:01.398
Porsha, stop. Wait!

1016
01:05:03.691 --> 01:05:06.194
Oh, I am one dead koala.

1017
01:07:06.981 --> 01:07:08.816
<i>And the hottest story today:</i>

1018
01:07:09.234 --> 01:07:13.863
Porsha Crystal was reportedly
fired from her father's show.

1019
01:07:15.323 --> 01:07:17.742
He fired my daughter?

1020
01:07:18.284 --> 01:07:20.620
My daughter?

1021
01:07:20.745 --> 01:07:22.956
Would you be quiet?
You've embarrassed me enough.

1022
01:07:23.039 --> 01:07:23.873
But, Daddy...

1023
01:07:23.957 --> 01:07:27.085
Now the whole world thinks
I got a talentless loser for a daughter.

1024
01:07:27.168 --> 01:07:29.212
Take her home.

1025
01:07:30.505 --> 01:07:32.465
Bring me Moon.

1026
01:08:07.542 --> 01:08:09.544
Ash? Now is not a good...

1027
01:08:09.627 --> 01:08:11.337
<i>Moon, I've got him!</i>

1028
01:08:11.421 --> 01:08:12.964
- What?
<i>- I got Calloway!</i>

1029
01:08:13.131 --> 01:08:15.174
Here, he wants to talk to you.

1030
01:08:15.466 --> 01:08:18.344
Your friend is even
more annoying than you are.

1031
01:08:18.511 --> 01:08:19.846
Don't listen to him.

1032
01:08:19.929 --> 01:08:21.806
We're heading to Redshore right now.

1033
01:08:21.889 --> 01:08:22.890
- You are?
<i>- Yes.</i>

1034
01:08:22.974 --> 01:08:25.602
My gosh.
Okay, this is great news, seriously.

1035
01:08:25.685 --> 01:08:27.270
You may have just saved my life here.

1036
01:08:34.527 --> 01:08:35.695
Okay.

1037
01:08:35.903 --> 01:08:37.322
Here we go.

1038
01:08:37.572 --> 01:08:39.490
Mr. Moon, what have you done?

1039
01:08:39.616 --> 01:08:42.201
Mr. Crystal. Aah!
I got some great news.,

1040
01:08:42.327 --> 01:08:45.371
Clay Calloway
is on his way here right now.

1041
01:08:45.455 --> 01:08:46.623
Everybody, out.

1042
01:08:47.999 --> 01:08:50.710
Okay, I think I know
what this might be about, and I...

1043
01:08:50.793 --> 01:08:52.378
You fired Porsha.

1044
01:08:52.462 --> 01:08:54.339
No. No. I never fired her.

1045
01:08:54.631 --> 01:08:56.090
You calling her a liar?

1046
01:08:56.174 --> 01:08:58.635
No, no, no, no,
she just got it wrong, is all.

1047
01:08:58.718 --> 01:09:01.179
I was only trying to help her
do the best she could...

1048
01:09:01.262 --> 01:09:04.557
And believe me,
I... I just wanted to do the right thing.

1049
01:09:04.641 --> 01:09:06.976
The right thing to do...

1050
01:09:07.060 --> 01:09:09.062
- is what I tell you to do!
- But I did!

1051
01:09:09.354 --> 01:09:11.481
I... I delivered a great show.

1052
01:09:11.564 --> 01:09:13.232
And Ca... Calloway, he's coming.

1053
01:09:13.316 --> 01:09:15.318
No, no, no! Stop! Stop!

1054
01:09:15.401 --> 01:09:16.401
No!

1055
01:09:16.527 --> 01:09:18.279
You really think I'd let a lowlife

1056
01:09:18.363 --> 01:09:21.115
little amateur loser like you

1057
01:09:21.324 --> 01:09:22.950
humiliate me?

1058
01:09:23.076 --> 01:09:24.535
Please! Please!

1059
01:09:24.702 --> 01:09:26.621
- You made me look bad.
- No, no!

1060
01:09:26.704 --> 01:09:27.705
I didn't mean to!

1061
01:09:27.914 --> 01:09:29.123
No!

1062
01:09:29.207 --> 01:09:30.875
So I'm gonna have to let you go.

1063
01:09:31.125 --> 01:09:33.503
What? Whoa!

1064
01:09:33.586 --> 01:09:35.338
Sir. Uh, sir, sir, sir.

1065
01:09:35.421 --> 01:09:37.507
I'm... I'm so sorry, um,
so sorry to bother you,

1066
01:09:37.590 --> 01:09:40.009
but, uh, you have a live
TV appearance in just a moment,

1067
01:09:40.134 --> 01:09:43.012
so it might be better
if we just put a pin in this right now.

1068
01:09:43.179 --> 01:09:44.972
Um...

1069
01:09:48.685 --> 01:09:50.603
You... you nearly killed me.

1070
01:09:50.687 --> 01:09:52.438
And I'll finish the job later.

1071
01:09:53.940 --> 01:09:56.401
No.

1072
01:09:56.484 --> 01:09:57.694
No! No!

1073
01:09:57.777 --> 01:09:59.445
Help!

1074
01:09:59.529 --> 01:10:02.115
Help! Jerry! Anyone!

1075
01:10:03.950 --> 01:10:05.493
No. Help, please!

1076
01:10:07.245 --> 01:10:08.621
Shh!

1077
01:10:09.247 --> 01:10:11.916
You need to get out of this city
and never, ever come back.

1078
01:10:11.999 --> 01:10:13.835
Do you understand? Never.

1079
01:10:13.918 --> 01:10:15.086
Okay, okay. I understand.

1080
01:10:15.169 --> 01:10:17.755
I told you you were not cut out for this.

1081
01:10:17.880 --> 01:10:18.880
He tried to kill me.

1082
01:10:18.923 --> 01:10:20.550
Yeah, and when he finds you're gone,

1083
01:10:20.633 --> 01:10:22.635
he'll have his thugs
looking all over for you.

1084
01:10:22.719 --> 01:10:24.929
Okay. Thank you, Suki.
I'm so, so...

1085
01:10:25.096 --> 01:10:26.347
Get out of here.

1086
01:10:31.102 --> 01:10:33.563
Uh, what did you say, Mr. Moon?

1087
01:10:33.646 --> 01:10:34.981
Get out! All of you!

1088
01:10:35.064 --> 01:10:36.733
- Get out of there right now!
- Hey!

1089
01:10:36.816 --> 01:10:38.818
There's no time to explain.
Just get the cast

1090
01:10:38.901 --> 01:10:41.195
and meet me back at the hotel!

1091
01:10:42.780 --> 01:10:45.908
And we're live in five, four,

1092
01:10:45.992 --> 01:10:47.869
three, two...

1093
01:10:52.248 --> 01:10:54.083
- Jerry, go get my snacks.
- Yes, sir.

1094
01:10:58.880 --> 01:11:01.007
What a great show we have...

1095
01:11:03.259 --> 01:11:05.636
Here to discuss the drama

1096
01:11:05.720 --> 01:11:08.055
- surrounding his new show...
- Sir! Uh, sir, sir, sir.

1097
01:11:08.139 --> 01:11:10.057
- Mr. Redshore City himself...
- What?

1098
01:11:10.141 --> 01:11:12.935
Please welcome Mr. Jimmy Crystal.

1099
01:11:13.311 --> 01:11:15.271
Come on out here, Jimmy.

1100
01:11:15.354 --> 01:11:18.316
- Don't make us beg.
- Moon got out. Find him.

1101
01:11:18.399 --> 01:11:21.027
Does this guy know
how to make an entrance or what?

1102
01:11:21.152 --> 01:11:24.447
Hey, everybody!
Good to see you.

1103
01:11:24.572 --> 01:11:26.324
<i>Linda, I got some hot news for you.</i>

1104
01:11:26.407 --> 01:11:27.950
<i>You look terrific.</i>

1105
01:11:28.034 --> 01:11:29.911
<i>It is so good to see you.</i>

1106
01:11:29.994 --> 01:11:32.538
<i>Thank you.</i>

1107
01:11:32.705 --> 01:11:34.123
<i>Oh, my gosh.</i>

1108
01:11:34.248 --> 01:11:37.210
Billionaire Magazine <i>Man of the Year</i>
<i>three years in a row,</i>

1109
01:11:37.376 --> 01:11:39.337
<i>owner of the largest...</i>

1110
01:11:39.420 --> 01:11:41.506
<i>theater chain in the world...</i>

1111
01:11:52.350 --> 01:11:53.684
Buster?

1112
01:11:53.893 --> 01:11:54.977
Ash?

1113
01:11:55.770 --> 01:11:58.272
- Ash, in here!
- Buster?

1114
01:12:00.608 --> 01:12:01.984
I... I'm stuck!

1115
01:12:02.860 --> 01:12:04.028
You got to be kidding me.

1116
01:12:04.111 --> 01:12:05.111
Hold still.

1117
01:12:05.321 --> 01:12:06.906
What are you doing in there?

1118
01:12:06.989 --> 01:12:08.991
Ash, the show's off.

1119
01:12:09.075 --> 01:12:11.327
- Crystal got mad and tried to kill me.
- What?

1120
01:12:12.870 --> 01:12:16.123
I thought you were his thugs
coming here to finish me off.

1121
01:12:18.084 --> 01:12:20.211
Oh, no. It's them.

1122
01:12:20.419 --> 01:12:22.004
Shh. Pretend we're not here.

1123
01:12:23.881 --> 01:12:25.967
The first time I leave home in 15 years,

1124
01:12:26.050 --> 01:12:27.635
and what do I find?

1125
01:12:27.718 --> 01:12:30.638
The show is off,
and this guy is hiding in a suitcase.

1126
01:12:30.763 --> 01:12:32.723
No, no, don't... don't open the door.

1127
01:12:33.015 --> 01:12:35.476
No, no, no.

1128
01:12:38.896 --> 01:12:41.065
Clay Calloway.

1129
01:12:42.733 --> 01:12:44.318
I remember you.

1130
01:12:46.237 --> 01:12:47.572
<i>Miss Crawly.</i>

1131
01:12:47.864 --> 01:12:50.366
- Pew, pew. Pew.
- Miss Crawly, wake up.

1132
01:12:50.449 --> 01:12:51.659
Wha... Mm, what?

1133
01:12:51.742 --> 01:12:53.494
Wake up. We got to get out of here.

1134
01:12:53.703 --> 01:12:56.330
- Coast is clear. Let's go.
- Come on, Miss Crawly. Come on.

1135
01:12:56.414 --> 01:12:57.790
Come on. Come on.

1136
01:12:57.874 --> 01:12:59.917
We'll all feel better
when we're safe at home.

1137
01:13:00.001 --> 01:13:01.168
You sure about that?

1138
01:13:01.419 --> 01:13:03.045
'Cause I can tell you,

1139
01:13:03.129 --> 01:13:05.006
running and hiding away

1140
01:13:05.089 --> 01:13:07.300
is not all that it's cracked up to be.

1141
01:13:07.466 --> 01:13:10.386
Well, we don't have a choice.

1142
01:13:10.720 --> 01:13:15.308
Yeah, well, all these years,
I thought the same,

1143
01:13:15.391 --> 01:13:17.852
but turns out there's always a choice.

1144
01:13:18.686 --> 01:13:21.355
Just never had the guts
to make the right one.

1145
01:13:22.189 --> 01:13:23.733
Know what I mean?

1146
01:13:24.025 --> 01:13:25.693
<i>Right? A victim.</i>

1147
01:13:25.776 --> 01:13:27.361
<i>I shut down my show</i>

1148
01:13:27.528 --> 01:13:30.907
<i>'cause of a talentless little twerp
called Buster Moon.</i>

1149
01:13:30.990 --> 01:13:33.576
<i>Seriously, you should've seen
this teeny, tiny loser.</i>

1150
01:13:33.659 --> 01:13:35.578
<i>Oh, and his pathetic amateur friends...</i>

1151
01:13:35.661 --> 01:13:37.246
<i>Let's just say, whatever Podunk town</i>

1152
01:13:37.330 --> 01:13:39.373
<i>they crawled out of,
that's where they belong,</i>

1153
01:13:39.540 --> 01:13:41.792
<i>'cause it sure ain't this great city.</i>

1154
01:13:47.089 --> 01:13:48.382
No.

1155
01:13:48.674 --> 01:13:50.635
I see, Clay's right.

1156
01:13:50.718 --> 01:13:53.554
What we're trying to do here,
it takes guts.

1157
01:13:55.348 --> 01:13:56.766
Guys, wait.

1158
01:13:56.849 --> 01:13:58.935
We... we cannot
let that... that...

1159
01:13:59.018 --> 01:14:00.853
that bully steal our hopes and dreams.

1160
01:14:00.937 --> 01:14:03.230
No, no, no. We are way past
singing and dancing now.

1161
01:14:03.314 --> 01:14:05.274
Look, I... I know
this might sound crazy.

1162
01:14:05.358 --> 01:14:07.693
- If we got the theater back...
- Oh, come on.

1163
01:14:07.777 --> 01:14:09.320
- Just for one night only.
- Seriously?

1164
01:14:09.403 --> 01:14:13.532
It's not like we can just sneak in there
and put the show on behind Crystal's back.

1165
01:14:14.200 --> 01:14:16.410
That is exactly what we're gonna do.

1166
01:14:17.036 --> 01:14:18.371
Yes!

1167
01:14:20.873 --> 01:14:23.167
Maybe it's, like, room service?

1168
01:14:24.502 --> 01:14:26.087
Open up or you're dead, Moon!

1169
01:14:26.170 --> 01:14:27.922
Okay, it's not room service.

1170
01:14:28.005 --> 01:14:30.591
You and your dumb friends
better not be hiding in there.

1171
01:14:30.675 --> 01:14:31.759
What are we gonna do?

1172
01:14:31.926 --> 01:14:33.469
Guys, we just got to be brave now.

1173
01:14:33.552 --> 01:14:35.304
Are you saying
we should fight these thugs?

1174
01:14:35.388 --> 01:14:36.889
No. They'll beat us to a pulp.

1175
01:14:38.307 --> 01:14:41.018
We're gonna put this show on
whether Crystal likes it or not.

1176
01:14:41.310 --> 01:14:44.146
But first, we're gonna jump
out that window.

1177
01:14:44.939 --> 01:14:46.023
What?

1178
01:14:46.190 --> 01:14:48.234
I'm beginning to like this guy.

1179
01:14:58.077 --> 01:15:00.955
Security. Yeah, we got nine suspects
loose on the river ride.

1180
01:15:01.163 --> 01:15:04.000
Repeat, nine suspects loose
on the river ride.

1181
01:15:04.208 --> 01:15:06.752
Hang on, everybody.

1182
01:15:06.961 --> 01:15:10.047
Uh, this is pool security.
I don't see anyone here. Over.

1183
01:15:10.256 --> 01:15:11.549
There!

1184
01:15:11.716 --> 01:15:13.676
They're heading east
through the back lot!

1185
01:15:13.759 --> 01:15:14.885
Go, go, go, go, go.

1186
01:15:15.678 --> 01:15:19.015
Oh, I wish I didn't have...
such teeny, tiny legs!

1187
01:15:29.900 --> 01:15:32.111
Thank you, Linda. Thank you.

1188
01:15:32.194 --> 01:15:33.738
Thanks, everybody.

1189
01:15:35.948 --> 01:15:37.116
Well?

1190
01:15:37.199 --> 01:15:39.869
No sign of 'em, sir.
We think they might have split town.

1191
01:15:51.589 --> 01:15:53.466
No one is supposed to be in here.

1192
01:15:54.467 --> 01:15:56.844
Uh, who are you?

1193
01:15:57.136 --> 01:15:58.763
We're the night cleaners.

1194
01:15:58.846 --> 01:16:00.181
Oh, I see.

1195
01:16:00.347 --> 01:16:02.558
Well, we don't need
any cleaning right now,

1196
01:16:02.641 --> 01:16:06.062
but it'd be better
if you didn't leave, so...

1197
01:16:06.187 --> 01:16:08.939
Mm, I don't suppose any of you
can tap-dance, huh?

1198
01:16:09.023 --> 01:16:10.775
Huh.

1199
01:16:10.858 --> 01:16:12.318
Well, let's move it, folks.

1200
01:16:17.114 --> 01:16:19.450
Here, Rosita. It's your role.

1201
01:16:22.912 --> 01:16:25.414
Miss Crawly, let's see if we can
get us a new green alien.

1202
01:16:25.498 --> 01:16:26.916
Yes, sir, Mr. Moon, sir.

1203
01:16:31.879 --> 01:16:33.631
<i>Rise and shine, sweetheart!</i>

1204
01:16:35.966 --> 01:16:37.593
Hey! You made it!

1205
01:16:37.676 --> 01:16:40.971
Yeah, well, uh, maybe
I overreacted a little before.

1206
01:16:41.055 --> 01:16:43.557
A little? You were, like,
a total drama queen back there.

1207
01:16:43.641 --> 01:16:44.934
Okay, we're all good now.

1208
01:16:45.017 --> 01:16:47.478
Wow, my dad's gonna flip
when he finds out about us.

1209
01:16:47.561 --> 01:16:49.438
- We're safe for now, but listen...
- Safe?

1210
01:16:49.688 --> 01:16:52.441
Uh, no. None of us are safe.

1211
01:16:52.525 --> 01:16:55.361
Mr. Moon, I know someone
who can protect us.

1212
01:16:55.486 --> 01:16:58.906
Right. Mm-hm. Yeah. Yeah.

1213
01:16:58.989 --> 01:17:00.449
Protection?

1214
01:17:00.533 --> 01:17:03.285
Say no more, son. We're on our way.

1215
01:17:34.358 --> 01:17:35.818
Good night, Porsha.

1216
01:17:38.154 --> 01:17:40.030
All right, be that way. I don't care.

1217
01:17:40.114 --> 01:17:41.824
Spoiled little brat.

1218
01:17:42.283 --> 01:17:44.535
All right, time to get us an audience.

1219
01:17:44.618 --> 01:17:47.955
Wait. Moon, as soon as you
start inviting folks in here,

1220
01:17:48.038 --> 01:17:50.291
hotel security will just shut
us down, right?

1221
01:17:50.457 --> 01:17:52.793
Oh, it's okay.
Rosita's got that covered.

1222
01:17:54.628 --> 01:17:57.006
Norman, release the piglets.

1223
01:18:08.100 --> 01:18:10.102
Hey, no!

1224
01:18:13.439 --> 01:18:17.359
All security, we have a situation
on floor 17.

1225
01:18:17.693 --> 01:18:20.613
Repeat, all security to floor 17.

1226
01:18:21.030 --> 01:18:24.533
This is the best day
of my life, Daddy! Whoo!

1227
01:18:24.700 --> 01:18:28.204
Repeat, everybody to floor 17!

1228
01:18:30.206 --> 01:18:32.374
<i>Wait, uh, is it on?</i>

1229
01:18:32.458 --> 01:18:34.001
<i>- It's on now.
- Now?</i>

1230
01:18:34.084 --> 01:18:35.524
<i>- Yes, now.
- Oh, yes, yes, yes, yes.</i>

1231
01:18:35.586 --> 01:18:36.962
<i>Before I blah, blah... Yeah, okay.</i>

1232
01:18:37.046 --> 01:18:38.422
<i>Good evening.</i>

1233
01:18:38.505 --> 01:18:40.633
<i>Uh, my name is Buster Moon,</i>

1234
01:18:40.925 --> 01:18:43.135
<i>and it is my great pleasure
to present to you,</i>

1235
01:18:43.219 --> 01:18:45.346
<i>for one night only
in the Crystal Tower Theater...</i>

1236
01:18:45.429 --> 01:18:47.139
Mr. Crystal's office.

1237
01:18:47.223 --> 01:18:48.599
This is Jerry speaking.

1238
01:18:49.141 --> 01:18:52.228
<i>a brand-new show</i>
<i>called</i> Out of This World.

1239
01:18:52.394 --> 01:18:55.147
<i>A musical space odyssey
featuring the return</i>

1240
01:18:55.231 --> 01:18:58.067
<i>of the legendary Clay Calloway.</i>

1241
01:18:58.484 --> 01:19:01.403
<i>That's right, Clay Calloway.</i>

1242
01:19:01.487 --> 01:19:04.740
<i>And what's more,
this show is completely free,</i>

1243
01:19:04.865 --> 01:19:07.368
<i>so step right up, folks,
and take your seats.</i>

1244
01:19:07.451 --> 01:19:10.537
<i>The journey of a lifetime
is about to begin.</i>

1245
01:19:10.829 --> 01:19:13.040
All right, folks, we all set back here?

1246
01:19:13.916 --> 01:19:15.251
There he is!

1247
01:19:15.376 --> 01:19:17.044
Dad.

1248
01:19:17.127 --> 01:19:18.963
- Come here.
- What are you wearing?

1249
01:19:19.046 --> 01:19:22.466
Oh, well, we're still doing
our community service, ain't we, lads?

1250
01:19:22.549 --> 01:19:23.549
- Yeah.
- That's right.

1251
01:19:23.759 --> 01:19:25.678
Oh, my gosh. He's here.

1252
01:19:25.928 --> 01:19:27.888
- Crystal's here?
- No.

1253
01:19:28.389 --> 01:19:29.723
My ice cream guy.

1254
01:19:30.099 --> 01:19:31.976
And he's sitting in the front row.

1255
01:19:32.184 --> 01:19:34.561
- Mr. Crystal! Mr. Crystal!
- Aah! Jerry!

1256
01:19:34.645 --> 01:19:36.480
- Mr. Crystal, wake up.
- I tried to stop him.

1257
01:19:36.563 --> 01:19:38.399
I'm so sorry to wake you up.
It's Moon.

1258
01:19:38.482 --> 01:19:40.943
He's taken over the theater,
and he's putting on a show.

1259
01:19:41.026 --> 01:19:43.028
He's what?

1260
01:19:52.204 --> 01:19:53.831
Okay, this is it, guys. You ready?

1261
01:19:53.914 --> 01:19:55.582
Oh, my gosh.
Are we really doing this?

1262
01:19:55.666 --> 01:19:57.042
You better believe it.

1263
01:19:57.126 --> 01:19:59.378
Yeah, big-time, baby!

1264
01:19:59.461 --> 01:20:00.587
Remember...

1265
01:20:00.671 --> 01:20:04.717
There's only one way
left to go, and that's up!

1266
01:20:04.842 --> 01:20:06.510
- Yeah! -
- Let's do it! Come on!

1267
01:20:06.593 --> 01:20:09.263
Gunter robot
activating piggy power.

1268
01:20:09.388 --> 01:20:11.348
- Beep-beep, boop-boop.
- Playback!

1269
01:20:16.395 --> 01:20:20.316
<i>All creatures great and small,</i>

1270
01:20:21.025 --> 01:20:24.028
<i>welcome to outer space.</i>

1271
01:20:33.829 --> 01:20:36.165
My name is Captain Rosita.

1272
01:20:36.999 --> 01:20:40.753
My mission: to find and rescue
a space explorer

1273
01:20:40.836 --> 01:20:43.589
who mysteriously
went missing long ago.

1274
01:20:44.256 --> 01:20:46.800
Captain, I am picking up
his signal.

1275
01:20:47.509 --> 01:20:49.762
Excellent. But from which planet?

1276
01:20:49.845 --> 01:20:51.847
I see four of them ahead.

1277
01:20:52.348 --> 01:20:55.934
It is impossible to know which one
the signal is, like, coming from.

1278
01:20:56.018 --> 01:20:57.102
I see.

1279
01:20:57.436 --> 01:20:59.188
Then I'll have to explore them all.

1280
01:20:59.313 --> 01:21:00.731
Take us down.

1281
01:21:01.607 --> 01:21:02.983
You've got this, big guy.

1282
01:21:03.067 --> 01:21:05.277
Remember what I said...
Just go with the flow.

1283
01:21:07.112 --> 01:21:09.782
Mission report.
I must take care,

1284
01:21:10.032 --> 01:21:13.285
for I have landed on the Planet of War.

1285
01:21:49.738 --> 01:21:51.115
That's my boy.

1286
01:22:29.611 --> 01:22:31.530
Yeah!

1287
01:22:33.282 --> 01:22:34.658
Give me that!

1288
01:22:34.741 --> 01:22:36.618
- And your costume. Now!
- Wait, what?

1289
01:22:36.702 --> 01:22:37.953
Take it off now!

1290
01:22:44.877 --> 01:22:46.420
We'll be at the theater soon.

1291
01:22:46.503 --> 01:22:48.922
I don't want to be there soon.
I want to be there now.

1292
01:22:49.006 --> 01:22:50.549
- We want to be there now.
- Yes, sir.

1293
01:23:35.802 --> 01:23:39.932
You see?
You will never be great, Johnny.

1294
01:23:44.478 --> 01:23:46.146
Oh, come on.

1295
01:24:20.138 --> 01:24:21.223
Yeah, that's more like it.

1296
01:24:49.001 --> 01:24:51.128
<i>This is Barry. Come in. Over.</i>

1297
01:24:51.211 --> 01:24:52.462
Yeah, go ahead, Barry.

1298
01:24:52.588 --> 01:24:56.300
Crystal's on site.
Repeat, Crystal is on site. Over.

1299
01:24:56.550 --> 01:24:58.051
Roger that.

1300
01:24:58.135 --> 01:25:00.429
Right, let's go to work.

1301
01:25:00.887 --> 01:25:02.431
Mission report.

1302
01:25:02.514 --> 01:25:04.600
My search takes me
to the second planet,

1303
01:25:04.933 --> 01:25:06.268
the Planet of Joy.

1304
01:25:06.351 --> 01:25:07.644
All right. Here we go, Porsha.

1305
01:25:07.853 --> 01:25:10.314
<i>Time to show the world
what you're really made of.</i>

1306
01:25:39.384 --> 01:25:41.178
Who the are you?
Where's my security?

1307
01:25:41.261 --> 01:25:43.055
We're security now, mate.

1308
01:25:43.138 --> 01:25:44.681
What?

1309
01:26:16.338 --> 01:26:17.338
Porsha!

1310
01:26:19.549 --> 01:26:20.549
Get off of there!

1311
01:26:21.385 --> 01:26:22.886
Don't you make me come out there!

1312
01:26:47.411 --> 01:26:48.578
You traitor.

1313
01:26:48.662 --> 01:26:50.789
That's it, I'm coming out there!

1314
01:26:53.375 --> 01:26:55.711
Miss Crawly put some cushions
and snacks there,

1315
01:26:55.794 --> 01:26:58.130
so you should be comfortable
till the show's over.

1316
01:26:58.505 --> 01:26:59.505
You little...

1317
01:27:35.751 --> 01:27:36.960
<i>Mission report.</i>

1318
01:27:37.043 --> 01:27:39.463
<i>No sign here
of the missing space explorer.</i>

1319
01:27:39.546 --> 01:27:41.131
<i>I'm moving to...</i>

1320
01:27:41.256 --> 01:27:42.924
- Ready, Gina?
- It's Meena.

1321
01:27:43.008 --> 01:27:44.885
- Wait, what is?
- Never mind.

1322
01:27:45.051 --> 01:27:46.678
Listen, find that feeling.

1323
01:27:46.762 --> 01:27:48.764
It is now or never.

1324
01:28:04.654 --> 01:28:07.240
Okay. I'm ready now.

1325
01:28:47.030 --> 01:28:48.740
Mr. Crystal, where are you?

1326
01:28:48.824 --> 01:28:51.117
I'm trapped somewhere
under the stage.

1327
01:28:51.201 --> 01:28:53.036
I'll find you, sir.

1328
01:28:53.119 --> 01:28:55.163
Mr. Crystal, I'm coming!

1329
01:30:00.604 --> 01:30:01.605
Yes!

1330
01:30:01.688 --> 01:30:04.274
I am gonna win
a ton of awards for this.

1331
01:30:08.612 --> 01:30:09.654
Hi.

1332
01:30:09.863 --> 01:30:11.323
Um, hi.

1333
01:30:11.406 --> 01:30:12.616
I'm Meena.

1334
01:30:12.699 --> 01:30:14.659
Oh. Um, Alfonso.

1335
01:30:15.285 --> 01:30:16.911
You... you were incredible.

1336
01:30:16.995 --> 01:30:18.496
So were you.

1337
01:30:18.580 --> 01:30:19.998
Um, what?

1338
01:30:20.248 --> 01:30:22.375
Oh. Uh, uh, never mind.

1339
01:30:22.459 --> 01:30:25.045
Um, want to meet up
after the show, maybe?

1340
01:30:25.211 --> 01:30:26.588
Uh, okay.

1341
01:30:27.380 --> 01:30:28.548
Okay, great. Bye.

1342
01:30:31.509 --> 01:30:33.803
Captain, we cannot land
on the last planet.

1343
01:30:33.887 --> 01:30:36.348
There is, like, a huge wormhole.

1344
01:30:36.431 --> 01:30:38.808
The ship will never make it.

1345
01:30:38.892 --> 01:30:40.477
You're right. It won't make it.

1346
01:30:41.561 --> 01:30:43.313
But I will.

1347
01:30:52.155 --> 01:30:53.365
Watch your fingers.

1348
01:31:14.636 --> 01:31:17.305
Rosita, you've got to jump.

1349
01:31:18.932 --> 01:31:20.767
Oh, honey.

1350
01:31:21.059 --> 01:31:22.352
Come on, Rosita.

1351
01:31:22.435 --> 01:31:23.978
- Look out!
- Whoa!

1352
01:31:24.062 --> 01:31:25.730
- Daddy, stop it!
- No!

1353
01:31:25.897 --> 01:31:27.899
- Mr. Moon!
- Mr. Crystal, no!

1354
01:31:29.025 --> 01:31:31.528
Well, I've got you now,
you lowlife little loser.

1355
01:31:31.695 --> 01:31:33.029
No, sir.

1356
01:31:33.113 --> 01:31:34.698
I'm not a loser.

1357
01:31:34.781 --> 01:31:36.783
We did what we came here to do.

1358
01:31:37.117 --> 01:31:40.704
And there is nothing
you can do or say to change that.

1359
01:31:45.041 --> 01:31:48.086
Oh, I can do whatever I want.

1360
01:32:26.958 --> 01:32:28.251
Aah! Whoa!

1361
01:33:14.798 --> 01:33:16.257
Woo-hoo!

1362
01:33:16.466 --> 01:33:18.468
I love you!

1363
01:33:18.551 --> 01:33:20.845
Yeah!

1364
01:33:20.929 --> 01:33:22.555
Oh, Mr. Moon, are you okay?

1365
01:33:22.639 --> 01:33:24.432
Yeah. Never better.

1366
01:33:24.516 --> 01:33:26.476
Uh, where's Ash and Clay?

1367
01:33:37.195 --> 01:33:38.696
Clay.

1368
01:33:38.780 --> 01:33:40.615
Clay, you back here?

1369
01:33:40.740 --> 01:33:41.783
We're on next.

1370
01:33:43.618 --> 01:33:45.245
You okay?

1371
01:33:45.328 --> 01:33:46.496
Uh-huh.

1372
01:33:48.122 --> 01:33:49.833
<i>Mission report.</i>

1373
01:33:50.041 --> 01:33:52.085
We have survived the wormhole.

1374
01:33:52.168 --> 01:33:54.212
- Yeah!
- Yeah.

1375
01:33:54.295 --> 01:33:56.965
And arrived on the last planet.

1376
01:33:57.465 --> 01:34:00.343
The missing space explorer
must be here somewhere,

1377
01:34:00.510 --> 01:34:03.638
but there's no sign of life
on my scanner.

1378
01:34:03.847 --> 01:34:05.431
That's your cue.

1379
01:34:05.515 --> 01:34:07.684
Clay, it's time to go on.

1380
01:34:07.767 --> 01:34:10.103
But I see no signs of life.

1381
01:34:10.186 --> 01:34:12.564
Nothing but an empty cave.

1382
01:34:12.730 --> 01:34:14.315
- Clay.
- Oh, no.

1383
01:34:14.399 --> 01:34:16.526
It's okay. Just sing.

1384
01:34:16.985 --> 01:34:18.862
- Your songs will carry you.
- No.

1385
01:34:19.112 --> 01:34:21.155
- This is a mistake.
- Please.

1386
01:34:21.239 --> 01:34:23.199
It's been so long.

1387
01:34:24.284 --> 01:34:25.743
I'm not ready.

1388
01:34:25.827 --> 01:34:26.995
I'm sorry.

1389
01:34:27.412 --> 01:34:28.705
I'm not ready.

1390
01:37:37.852 --> 01:37:39.270
<i>Mission accomplished.</i>

1391
01:37:39.353 --> 01:37:40.480
<i>We're heading home.</i>

1392
01:38:01.918 --> 01:38:04.003
- Hey, Mr. Moon!
- Come on!

1393
01:38:04.087 --> 01:38:05.755
- Get out here, Moon.
- Come on out here!

1394
01:38:44.627 --> 01:38:47.547
Jimmy!

1395
01:38:48.089 --> 01:38:50.383
Oh, my gosh,
listen to that crowd.

1396
01:38:50.466 --> 01:38:52.385
You are a genius.

1397
01:38:52.510 --> 01:38:54.178
Yeah, you really are a genius, sir.

1398
01:38:55.763 --> 01:38:58.474
Yeah, you got that right, Linda.

1399
01:39:01.727 --> 01:39:03.771
<i>Thank you, thank you.</i>

1400
01:39:03.855 --> 01:39:06.232
<i>Too kind. I appreciate it, really.</i>

1401
01:39:06.315 --> 01:39:08.025
<i>I... I do.</i>

1402
01:39:08.151 --> 01:39:10.444
<i>Look, I am very proud of this show.</i>

1403
01:39:10.528 --> 01:39:13.406
<i>We did great work here. Great work.</i>

1404
01:39:13.531 --> 01:39:17.076
<i>And my good friend, Clay...
Great to have him back, right?</i>

1405
01:39:17.243 --> 01:39:19.162
<i>Yeah!</i>

1406
01:39:19.579 --> 01:39:22.999
<i>And listen, I look forward
to seeing this show run</i>

1407
01:39:23.082 --> 01:39:26.002
<i>at my theater for many,
many years to come.</i>

1408
01:39:26.794 --> 01:39:27.879
<i>Right, Moon?</i>

1409
01:39:29.755 --> 01:39:31.924
<i>Moon?</i>

1410
01:39:40.308 --> 01:39:42.560
Officers, arrest that wolf.

1411
01:39:44.896 --> 01:39:46.731
Wait! He's innocent!

1412
01:39:46.814 --> 01:39:48.065
Mr. Crystal, please!

1413
01:39:48.149 --> 01:39:49.358
I love you!

1414
01:40:57.885 --> 01:40:59.095
Stop the bus!

1415
01:41:00.346 --> 01:41:01.555
Whoa!

1416
01:41:01.639 --> 01:41:03.599
- What is it?
- What happened?

1417
01:41:03.724 --> 01:41:05.309
- What's going on?
- Ow!

1418
01:41:05.393 --> 01:41:07.436
I just got a call from The Majestic.

1419
01:41:07.520 --> 01:41:09.272
They think your show is fantastic,

1420
01:41:09.355 --> 01:41:11.607
and they want to put it on
at their theater.

1421
01:41:13.526 --> 01:41:15.736
Well, what do you say, Mr. Calloway?

1422
01:41:15.820 --> 01:41:16.988
You in?

1423
01:44:26.510 --> 01:44:27.678
Oh!

